# Block Generic Settings Contract

Use the canonical Interface Builder path only (`baserow-app/lib/interface/types.ts`, `registry.ts`, `block-config-types.ts`, `components/interface/settings/blockSettingsRegistry.tsx`).

## Canonical keys

- Use `table_id` and `view_id` (never `sourceTableId` / `sourceViewId`).
- Use block-prefixed `*_use_mock` flags for demo mode.
- Use `record_limit` where shared; otherwise block-prefixed `*_max_items` / `*_max_posts`.
- Field mapping keys must be `*_field_id` with optional `*_field` fallback.

## Field resolution order (required)

1. `*_field_id` (resolve to actual field name)
2. `*_field` (stored field name fallback)
3. Existing heuristic discovery (`pickFieldName`)

## Baseline settings for data-driven custom blocks

Unless clearly not relevant, each block should expose:

- `title` + `subtitle`
- source table selection (`table_id`; `view_id` when supported)
- demo toggle (`*_use_mock`)
- item limit (`record_limit` or `*_max_items`)
- filter/search/grouping controls when block supports those concepts

## Runtime behavior rules

- Settings UI must be wired to runtime behavior (not cosmetic only).
- `table_id` must override name-discovery; discovery remains fallback.
- Do not silently show demo records as live data.
- If demo mode is off and live data is unavailable, show empty/unconfigured state.

## Validation and persistence rules

- Keep marketing/custom block validation non-blocking for unconfigured state.
- New config keys must be included in `BlockConfig` and defaults where applicable.
- Do not introduce parallel config systems or duplicate schema names.
